cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.CC, cs.DL, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new self-index data structure based on LZ77/LZ-End for efficient text extraction and pattern search. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses the ability to search for occurrences of a pattern within a compressed text collection. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the time and space complexity of the proposed self-index compared to existing ones. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is a possible category as the paper deals with compressing and storing large text collections. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the efficient storage and retrieval of text data using the proposed self-index.
